text: Chaco frog may refer to: * Chaco horned frog (Chacophrys pierottii), a frog in the family Ceratophryidae found in the Chaco of northern Argentina, eastern Bolivia, and western Paraguay * Chaco tree frog (Hypsiboas raniceps), a frog in the family Hylidae found in Argentina, Bolivia, Brazil, Colombia, French Guiana, Paraguay, and Venezuela Category:Animal common name disambiguation pages
title: Chaco frog
